					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On a Slab set up near the sluice of the lake in the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Dēvarāya, (son of Vijayarāya-uḍaiyar) Śaka 1352: 1430 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The details of the date viz., Śaka 1352, Sādhāraṇa, Āvaṇi 12 are not sufficient for verification. The record may be assigned to c. 15th Century on grounds of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It records the permission granted by Tirumalai-nāyakkar, son of Kanyāsūryaṉ Vaḍakku-nāyakkar and his horseman of the Kannaḍa country for the excavation of the lake called Sukumāṟaṉ-ēri at Neṟ-kuṇam. The village Neṟkuṇam was held as <hi rend="italic">jīvita-paṟṟu</hi> by the king himself. </p>						

						</summary>
